About the weekly BCS checks:
text: Feeling a little bit funky about weekly BCS checks not being scheduled the way one might expect: Were last done Wednesday 1/26/22 at 4AM (pretty much "one week" (= 7 days) ago). Not scheduled to be done again until Saturday 2/5/22 2AM...10 days since last done. Guidance document (what the BAS running conditions call for) is SLAC-I-040-007 which states: "The ACR Control Room Operators complete...each week..." Generally a week starts on Sunday and ends on Saturday, so in that spirit we will be doing the checks "each week"...but this still feels funky. For example we could do them again on Sunday 2/6/22, then not again until Saturday 2/19/22...fulfilling the "each week" requirement, but having not done them for 13 days. It kind of feels like that is what is happening here.

LCLS User Meeting Notes 2/2/2022

 

TMO (Photon MD - KB1 Realignment)

2/4 – 2/7, 7:30am – 7:30pm

SECONDARY, 10 Hz

User Requirements:

600 eV (M), 1 keV (T), 880 eV (W), 1.5 keV (Th)

6.2 GeV

Likely need to pull out undulators for the first shift to reduce higher order harmonics.

May adjust electron energy to accommodate 1.5 keV for Thursday shift.

 

XCS (Photon MD - Checkout)

2/4, 7:30am – 7:30pm

User Requirements:

9.5 keV, 10.515 GeV

 

XPP (LY51)

2/4 – 2/7, 6am – 6pm

Chirality dependence of charge density wave in axionic Ta2Se8I

When this material is cooled, it modulates the charge density of electrons in the crystal structure. The goal of this experiment is to characterize the chirality (handedness) of the charge density wave generated by this modulation using X-ray diffuse scattering.  

User Requirements:

9.5 keV, 10.515 GeV

~30 fs

Need X-ray stability – emphasis on pointing stability, but also prefer pulse intensity to be stable.

 

CXI (LZ07)

2/4 – 2/7, 6am – 6pm

Ultrafast Events in Bacteriophytochromes

Phytochromes are a family of photoreceptors used as light-regulated enzymes involved in various plant processes. Photochrome-like photoreceptors found in bacteria, called bacteriophytochromes, serve as powerful model systems for the more complex plant phytochromes. After studying bacteriophytochromes at SACLA using 30 Hz FEL beam, users will investigate these phenomena using 120 Hz rate available at LCLS.  

User Requirements:

9.5 keV

10.515 GeV

 

MEC (LX83)

2/1, 2/3, 7:30 pm – 9 am

Phase transition behavior of a particular compound.

User Requirements:

11 keV, 11.315 GeV

 

 

MEC (LX64)

2/5 – 2/8, 6 pm – 6 am

Study structure of ferrous oxide and magnesium oxide in solution and melting under high pressure.

User Requirements:

Will start first shift at 17 keV and checkout performance.

Will go to 15 keV, 13.213 GeV if performance is inadequate for experiment.
